results.name: workforce-management-information-department-for-education
results.notes:
Monthly management information on staff numbers and paybill costs in the Department for Education family.

For workforce numbers, both payroll and non-payroll (contingent labour, including consultants) information is provided, split between full-time equivalents (FTE) and headcount, with payroll staff numbers mapped to standard Civil Service grades.

For costs, payroll paybill information is broken down into its component parts i.e. salaries, allowances, employers pensions contributions etc. For non-payroll costs, these are split between costs for consultancy and those of other non-payroll workers.

Staffing numbers are as at the last day of the month for the reference month. Cost information is that for the reference month. For baseline 2010/11, staffing numbers are as at 31 March 2011, and paybill costs are for the financial year 2010/11.
results.title: Workforce Management Information - Department for Education

results.name: 2018-2019-centre-for-environment-fisheries-aquaculture-science-cefas-clip-vanuatu-land-waste-au
results.notes:
This dataset contains 2 csv files. Solid_waste_audit_Vanuatu_Abundance.csv 
reports solid waste abundance and composition data from households and 
commercial activities expressed in number of items, weight or volume. 
Solid_waste_audit_Vanuatu_Metadata.csv reports the results of interviews done 
when solid waste samples were collected to gather metadata about household 
occupants social and behavioural metadata, including the fate of solid waste 
not collected through the official waste management service.

Waste audits were conducted between November and December 2018 in Efate island 
(Port Vila, 50 samples; and the rural community of Black Sands, 35 samples), 
Espiritu Santo islands (Luganville and rural communities, 49 samples) and two 
outer islands: Lelepa (Efate, 61 samples) and Ifira (Efate, 10 samples). 
Commercial activities were also audited (30 in Port Vila; and 15 in 
Luganville). A READ-ME text file contains the description of columns content 
for the two csv files.
